      "name": "Cobalt Strike",
      "description": "Cobalt Strike is a commercial penetration testing tool that is widely abused by threat actors for post-exploitation, lateral movement, and C2 operations. In this campaign, Cobalt Strike was deployed using GoRed and trojanized Sysinternals tools, including Sysmon and Process Explorer.",
